About Me

Thank you for taking time to look at my work! Im a classic rock music fan, a coffee addict, a foodie, and a traveler. I am also an educator, speaker, and consultant.

Ive been fascinated by math from a young age. The ability to work with numbers is one of the most useful and essential skills one can develop in school and college. I also believe that mathematical sciences can be fun and exciting to learn if you teach them the right way.

Ive been a school teacher for over ten years. During that time, Ive developed different teaching approaches, created an online course, and helped hundreds of students to fall in love with mathematical sciences. I believe that learning should not be a repeatable or tedium. It should evoke passion and give you another viable reason to wake up in the mornings no matter how young or old.

Teaching through Values

Education is my chosen career path, and I believe its a great privilege. I feel so grateful for the ability to work with students and to teach the next generation of thought and practice leaders. I also work with teachers, helping them build new education strategies. In doing so, I know that my work will have an impact on so many college students, even the ones I dont teach personally.

I believe in personalized learning. I also think there are no dull subjects. Therefore, I do my best to make the learning process interesting for everyone, to encourage exploration and research, and to teach students to apply this knowledge not only in college but also in business and everyday life.

SpeakFirst Middle School Coach

Ive been lucky to work as a middle school debate coach in a Birmingham city school during my year of service with Impact America in Alabama. I worked with my co-coaches twice a week for an academic year, creating and implementing lesson plans for 12 middle school students.

Miller Writing Center Tutor

The Miller Writing Center is a part of Auburns Office of University Writings initiative. It is focused on increasing the quality of students writing. To achieve that, MWC tutors dont simply edit the papers, but interact with students one-on-one to guide them.
